---

In my opinion, finances and problem-solving skills are the most important things that can be taught to a person. I believe that it is important to be able to manage your money and make the most of what you have. Money is one of the most important factors in life. If you don't have it, you likely won't be happy.  The happiness levels of the impoverished are incredibly low.  If more people learned how to manage finances from a young age, there would be less poverty as people wouldn't go wasting their money on things they don't need or living above their means.

The second thing that is extremely important is the ability to solve problems. Life is full of problems. If you can't solve them, you will have a hard time getting through life. Many people encounter problems in life and freeze, not knowing what to do.  Those who know how to problem solve generally have a better chance of success. They give up less, as they are always looking for solutions. 

Unfortunately, I was not taught anything about finances in any of my school classes.  It would have been great for me, as I have not always been good with my finances. I have made a lot of mistakes and I have learned from them. Thankfully, I was taught to problem solve. I solved my financial problems with these skills and now I live a stable and secure lifestyle. I am very happy with my life. I was able to find a job before I finished college, and then after I found out I hated that job, I was able to switch my line of work completely and start my own business. There were many challenges with starting a business, but I did it, and I was successful. I don't use my computer science degree, but I am happier for it. I am glad I learned how to problem-solve.

Surely there are many other important skills, but problem-solving and financial skills are a surefire way to get through life decently.
